    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-16T11:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-16T11:30:00-05:00" n="268"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <head>268. Telegram From the Embassy in Iran to the Department of State<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d268fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1950–1954, 788.00/8–1653.
                        Secret. Repeated <gloss target="#t_NIACT_1">NIACT</gloss> to London and to
                        Beirut for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HLW_1">Henderson</persName>.
                        Received at 1:09 p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Tehran</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1953-08-16T20:00:00+03:30">August 16, 1953, 8 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>348. Flight by Shah and uncertainty Zahedi actions presumably leave <persName
                        corresp="#p_MM_1">Mosadeq</persName> victor in protracted and
                    Persian-mannered campaign eliminate Shah as political force in country. Embassy
                    considers quite possible <persName corresp="#p_MM_1">Mosadeq</persName> may
                    establish regency to provide needed interim before eventual proclamation Iranian
                    republic.</p>
                <p>Believe under circumstances and pending Department decisions upon varied policy
                    matters apparent as result new situation that Ambassador’s immediate return
                    desirable. However, as situation may be still fluid suggest Ambassador return
                    prepared to continue be unwell in order avoid any official interviews if
                    situation warrants. Attitude, statements and actions <persName corresp="#p_MM_1"
                        >Mosadeq</persName> government in next few days likewise will assist
                    Department in determining lines to be followed.<note n="2" xml:id="d268fn2"
                        >Telegram 370 from Tehran, August 17, reported that <persName
                            corresp="#p_HLW_1">Henderson</persName> arrived in Tehran that day at 6
                        p.m. (Ibid.)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_MGH_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGH_1">Mattison</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
